textBeforeTable: Since the game is still months from release, the demo limits players to a portion of the game available in the closed alpha test. As specified in one of the demo's loading screens, characters are limited to level 15, the number of quests and missions is limited, some professions lack a full range of abilities, and guild and trading features are not yet implemented. GameSpot DLX (registration required), but will now access the additional data for the demo rather than halting at the title screen. Here's word on the demo, which is slated to run through the 15th: up on GameSpot, where the small 61 KB client stub has been available from In a surprise move, the promised E3 demo of Guild Wars has gone live a bit earlier than the original plan to launch the E3-concurrent demo of ArenaNet's upcoming MMORPG.
